Hiring a SUV in Dubai

Over time, SUV rent in Dubai have begun to grow in popularity all over the world. The comfort, space, and high driving position they provide are unmatched, and their safety features are spectacular. SUV for rent in Dubai are the most popular type of vehicle in the UAE and they are loved by all.

In fact, the right and cheap SUV rental Dubai will have a better presence on the road than many sports cars. For example, the, local legends, the Nissan Patrol and the Toyota Land-Cruiser. Two of the best-selling cars in the UAE, are large-size SUVs. Their wide stance and tall position garner heaps of respect on the road, and tell other drivers that they are not to be messed with.

SUV for Rent in Dubai

SUVs are a staple on UAE roads, from the beloved Nissan Patrol and Toyota Land-Cruiser, to more exotic vehicles, like the Mercedes G63 AMG, or Bentley Bentayga, the SUV is by far the most commanding vehicle you will find in the UAE. All the SUVs we offer have the features you need, from strong air conditioning, to plenty of storage space, as well as a plethora of safety features to ensure your mind is at ease when driving. The SUVs offered really do have it all.

Want to rent an SUV in Dubai?

If you’re looking to rent, chances are, we’ve got exactly what you’re looking for. From large, premium SUVs amongst the likes of the Mercedes Benz G63 AMG, to more compact SUVs like the Creta by Hyundai, we’ve got it all! There’s no better way to travel in Dubai than an SUV. The large body of the vehicle coupled with its ride height makes you feel as though you’re the “King of the Road”, and at OneClickDrive.com, we offer a plethora of SUVs for you to rent or lease.

SUV Car Rental Dubai Deals - Guaranteed!

OneClickDrive offers direct-from-supplier rates. Zero commission, no booking fees and free from any hidden charges. The prices for SUVs below include standard mileage and insurance. Weekend discounts and hourly rentals available upon request. Get in touch with us via phone or WhatsApp to book an SUV today!

Frequently Asked Questions

The cost to renting a SUV in Dubai is about AED 299 per day and AED 6950 per month inclusive of all charges. Car rental rates are vary depends on the length of rentals as some companies provide cheaper rates also up to AED 30 per day for long term rental or lease.

The rental process is the same for all cars. The minimum legal age to rent a car is 21 years, however, some exotic cars may require for the renter to be 23 or even 25 years of age in some cases.For UAE residents, you will need a copy of your Emirates ID and Driver’s License. For tourists, you will need a copy of your passport, visit visa (with entry stamp), driver’s license (from your country of residence) as well as an international driver’s license (IDP).Please note that while most companies only accept credit cards for the security deposit in the form of a pre-authorization block, some companies also accept cash or debit cards.

OneClickDrive.com offers an incredibly large selection of SUVs. From SUVs that can outrun most regular cars you see on the road, such as the Mercedes G63, Porsche Cayenne Turbo, and Lamborghini or luxurious SUVs with plenty of pulling power, like the Land-Rover Range-Rover and Rolls-Royce Cullinan, for those who want to experience the most premium ride there is to offer.There are also mid-size high-end SUVs like the Maserati Levante or Land-Rover Range-Rover Sport. Even if you’re looking for the largest SUVs for storage, we offer the Nissan Patrol, which is the self-proclaimed king of UAE roads, the Toyota Land Cruiser, GMC Yukon and Chevrolet Tahoe. Not only this, but we offer plenty of simpler, regular SUVs, like the Nissan Pathfinder, Toyota Prado, Toyota Fortuner, Mitsubishi Pajero, and many more! We even offer small vehicles like Hyundai Creta, Toyota Rush, Kia Seltos etc. There are plenty of options to choose from. On oneclickdrive.com there’s an rent car SUV available for any and all purposes.

Yes of course! Car rental companies allow their vehicles to be driven anywhere within the UAE, with the exception of Jebel Jais, Jebel Hafeet, and within the desert regions. The drive from Dubai to Abu Dhabi is approximately 150km away so if you’re doing a return trip you’ll most likely do over 300km on the journey. Renting an SUV from oneclickdrive.com instead of buying one allows you to enjoy the car without having to worry about maintenance and any other faults you may experience upon using the car. When it comes to buying an economical SUV, you can consider buying a used car or new car but the depreciation factor and the running cost may turn out to be higher than expected. Leasing a car on a long-term basis is definitely worth looking into.Furthermore, when it comes to renting a vehicle long-term, you’re paying for what you use, not for the car as a whole, hence it is better from an economical standpoint as well.
